message: Merge branch 'feature/620-bytecode' into develop

Implement Multiple Returns

This implements the final piece of the jigsaw: multiple returns.  These
are implemented without the use of position operators.  Instead,
locations are now permitted to have zero or more types.  This works well
for statements, which can now have zero types (instead of void type);
also, of course, it works well for expressions with multiple return
values.

Tidy up verification tests

Yet more tidying up of the verification tests.  I went through a whole
load (though not all) of them and reclassified them.  In some cases, the
tests themselves were invalid and I fixed them.
Final fix for #662

Remove "no" quantifier #668

The "no" quantifier was (and has previously) causing problems.  To be
honest, this quantifier is not required.  Removing it was very
straightforward, and all test cases have been updated to use "all"
instead of "no".

More tidying of valid/invalid test cases

Went through a number of valid / invalid test cases tidying them up.
For example, unignoring some which were actually passing.  Adding
missing output for others.  And correcting syntax errors in some which
arose due to previous changes in the language syntax.

Fix for #662
